title: Study: 'Keto-like' diet may be linked to double the risk of cardiovascular events
description: A low-carb, high-fat "keto-like" diet may be linked to higher levels of "bad" cholesterol and double the risk of cardiovascular events such as blocked arteries, heart attacks and strokes, according to new research.

title: CNN anchor Kasie Hunt gives birth in surprise 13-minute labor
description: CNN anchor and chief national affairs analyst Kasie Hunt and husband Matthew Mario Rivera welcomed their second child to the world last week in an unforgettable way.

title: Rampant Liverpool humiliates Manchester United with stunning 7-0 Premier League derby win
description: This season has been one of trials and tribulations for Liverpool and its beleaguered fans, but there may still be light at the end of the tunnel as Jurgen Klopp's men put in a truly scintillating performance to tear Manchester United apart at Anfield.

title: Fire rips through Rohingya refugee camp in Bangladesh leaving thousands homeless
description: A massive fire has ripped through a Rohingya refugee camp in Bangladesh's southern district of Cox's Bazar on Sunday, leaving around 12,000 people homeless, local Superintendent of Police Mohammad Mahfuzul Islam told CNN.

title: Max Verstappen cruises to victory in season-opening Bahrain Grand Prix
description: Max Verstappen cruised to victory at the Bahrain Grand Prix on Sunday, stamping his authority on the season in the opening race.

title: After serving 38 years for a murder he didn't commit, this man has finally been declared innocent
description: Maurice Hastings, a man wrongfully convicted of a 1983 robbery-homicide and sexual assault, has been declared innocent by a California judge.

title: Passenger dies after severe turbulence on private business jet, aviation officials say
description: One person died as a result of severe turbulence on a private business jet that was diverted to the Bradley International Airport in Windsor Locks, Connecticut, on Friday, according to aviation officials.

title: Jill Biden says the idea of a competency test for elderly politicians is 'ridiculous'
description: First lady Jill Biden pushed back on concerns about President Joe Biden's age and dismissed a proposal by Republican presidential candidate Nikki Haley for politicians over age 75 to take a mental competency test.

title: Bakhmut deputy mayor: 'The enemy blows everything to the ground'
She flatlined three times, lost both legs and had a failing heart. Yet she told doctors she's 'the luckiest person on this planet'
description: Her smile is bright, cheery, sometimes goofy and always contagious. But pictures can't completely capture her upbeat, positive vibe. At 21, Claire Bridges has a mature spirit that amazes those who love her as well as the doctors who had to operate on her heart and remove both legs to save her life.

title: 5 people shot near a gun buyback event at a Los Angeles beach
description: Five people were injured in a shooting at a Los Angeles beach Saturday -- a few miles from where city officials had hosted a gun buyback event earlier in the day, according to the Los Angeles Police Department and Los Angeles City Councilmember Tim McOsker.

title: Best donkey, scariest doll and Austin Butler's Elvis accent -- CNN's take on the best in film
description: The Oscars are considered the highlight of awards season, but its categories are so rigid -- best actress? Best costuming? How about freakiest killer doll nightmare and best performance by a donkey? We at CNN's culture desk are honoring the best and most memorable movies of the year with our own awards that the Academy Awards won't touch.

title: Jon Jones warns some of his 'best performances' are yet to come after dominant UFC heavyweight title win over Ciryl Gane
description: Jon Jones won the UFC heavyweight title in some style on Saturday, defeating France's Ciryl Gane with a first-round submission following a three-year absence and a step up in weight division.

title: It's Hell Week on Wall Street
description: Wall Street investors are gearing up for their version of Hell Week — a torrent of jobs data coming over the next few days could easily lead to volatile market swings.

title: Russian reservists fought with 'shovels' during assault on Ukrainian stronghold, says UK Ministry of Defence
Greek prime minister apologizes over train collision amid public fury
description: Greek Prime Minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis has apologized for one of the country's worst train crashes in years, saying "We cannot, will not, and must not hide behind human error."

title: The least-visited national parks in the United States in 2022
description: America's least-visited national park is quite a distance from mainland US shores. Almost 5,000 miles away, in fact.

title: #StopWillow is taking TikTok by storm. Can it actually work?
description: When Elise Joshi posted a TikTok video about the Alaska oil drilling project known as Willow in early February, she didn't have high hopes it would go viral.

title: Alex Murdaugh's risky testimony ultimately brought him down
description: Convicted former attorney Alex Murdaugh's decision to take the stand at his double murder trial was not entirely surprising given his family's legal legacy stretching back to the early 1900s in coastal South Carolina.

title: Kyiv says it will use seized Russian assets to rebuild country
How a group of digital activists are helping earthquake survivors in Turkey and Syria find shelter
description: Five digital activists have created a website to help provide shelter to survivors of the earthquake in Syria and Turkey that left millions homeless amid freezing winter temperatures.

title: US evaluating Ukrainian pilots for possible F-16 training
description: The US is working with Ukrainian pilots in the United States to determine how long it would take to train them to fly F-16 fighter jets, three sources briefed on the matter told CNN.

title: 4 dead, 40,000 flee homes as floods hit Malaysia
description: Rescue efforts are underway in parts of Malaysia after seasonal floods killed at least four people and displaced more than 40,000.

title: Turkey is blocking NATO's expansion. It could backfire and hand Putin a propaganda coup
description: When Sweden and Finland declared their intention to join NATO last May, it was seen by many as a poke in the eye for Russia and evidence of a shift in European thinking. Historically, both countries had committed to non-alignment with NATO as a way of avoiding provoking Moscow. The invasion of Ukraine changed that.

title: Countries agree historic oceans treaty to protect the high seas
description: Nearly 200 countries have agreed to a legally-binding treaty to protect marine life in international waters, which cover more than half of the planet's surface, but have long been essentially lawless.

title: Wave of suspected poison attacks on schoolgirls sparks protests in Iran
description: Worried parents protested in Iran's capital Tehran and other cities on Saturday over a wave of suspected poison attacks that have affected schoolgirls in dozens of schools, according to Iranian news agencies and social media videos.

title: China sets growth target of 'around 5%' for 2023 as it aims to bounce back after years of zero-Covid
description: China has set an official economic growth target of "around 5%" for 2023, as it seeks to revive the world's second largest economy after a year of tepid growth because of pandemic measures.

title: Hong Kong model's death and dismemberment resurfaces memories of past horrors
description: The postcard image of Hong Kong is one of glitzy skyscrapers against lush mountains, dim sum restaurants and investment bankers in suits.
